    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD) retains the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering linear power through the rev range. The chassis features a front-mid engine layout with a 50/50 weight distribution and a sophisticated four-wheel double-wishbone suspension system for exceptional lateral grip. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a 5-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential. This example is mechanically sound with a healthy vacuum system and consistent compression across both rotors. It features tasteful cooling modifications, including an upgraded dual-pass aluminum radiator and a downpipe to manage thermal loads, ensuring the apex seals remain within optimal operating temperatures during spirited driving. The interior and exterior show honest wear consistent with a well-maintained enthusiast vehicle.",
